<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-804-364  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 804 364.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDN  Oct 12 1989 v34 n21 p161(7).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Simulation helps you debug I/O software for embedded systems.andO;(microcontroller simulation part 2)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gezelius, Anders.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>This second of two articles on microcontroller simulationillustrates the use o simulation in debugging complex, real-timeembedded software systems.andP;  Simulators facilitate thedesign-verification testing of such real-time systems bygenerating desired event (test) sequences and observing thesystem's responses under test.andP;  The described simulation problemconsists of the design of a remote data-acquisition unit thatrepeatedly samples the voltage of four analog inputs every 35ms,transmitting the results to another system over a 2000 bps seriallink.andP;  Details of the simulation tools and process are described.andO;The completion of the simulation should be followed by regressiontesting for each product that has undergone changes.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     FirmwareMicroprogrammed ControlSimulation of Computer SystemsCircuit DesignProgrammable controllers.andO;Feature:   illustrationchartprogram.andO;Caption:   Debugging of data-acquisition through simulation. (chart)The controller uses this format to initiate A/D conversions.andO;(chart)Operational code for data-acquisition unit. (program)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>